  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6480 sitting just below the massive -7994M gamma wall at 6500, dealers are in active buying mode to hedge their short gamma exposure, creating strong upward pressure toward that key resistance level. The breakout regime combined with heavy negative gamma clustering between 6400-6500 means any push above 6500 will trigger aggressive dealer buying that could propel price toward the 6605 positive gamma ceiling where selling pressure kicks in. Watch 6500 as the critical inflection point - a break above unleashes momentum-driven buying, while failure here likely sends price cascading back through the 6450/6400 negative gamma walls with dealers amplifying the selloff.",
